first because theres no fire hydrant in the parking lot we 
cant get any water to the cars los angeles county fire 
inspector john lenihan said 
county fire capt garry oversby said later that water was 
rerouted from hydrants nearby 
it was not immediately known whether the blaze began in a 
vehicle or on the vegetation in bonnelli park but the flames 
leaped from car to car oversby said 
the fire was reported shortly after 2 pm in an overflow 
parking area for raging waters amusement park less than one mile 
away the park was not evacuated and no one was injured 
raging waters is 44 acres five million gallons and tons of 
fun for everyone said a taperecorded message at the park about 
25 miles northeast of los angeles the park features 12 water 
slides a freshwater surf pool and a riverrafting ride 
damage was estimated at 50000 oversby said 
