communities isolated by flooding after two hurricanes officials 
said 
the government newspaper el nacional citing preliminary 
reports said 27 people died 
much of the southern half of the country was affected by 
hurricanes debby and kristy from veracruz on the east to the west 
coast resorts and chiapas on the border with guatemala 
officials said most of the victims were killed in mudslides or 
were swept away by swollen rivers an estimated 50000 people were 
evacuated from their homes 
hurricane debby struck on friday kristy affected the pacific 
coast for several days but never hit land and moved out to sea 
in veracruz about 150 miles northeast of mexico city about 
25000 people were left homeless state government spokesman raul 
torres said sunday as many as 10000 residents of alamo were 
forced to leave their homes torres said 
