<TEXT>
despite initial skepticism us officials are 
pleased with an experiment in which 17 american financial experts 
moved into liberian government offices to bring order to the 
african nations chaotic financial system 
liberia a country founded by freed american slaves a century 
and a half ago has always had a special relationship with the 
united states and president samuel k doe turned to washington in 
1987 after his fiscal problems ran out of control 
corruption was rampant government checks were bouncing civil 
servants were being paid months late and bureaucrats were spending 
money without regard to budgetary limits some government 
contractors were not paid for work performed while others received 
checks they were not entitled to 
in january 1987 when secetary of state george p shultz made a 
brief stop in monrovia doe told him i need help 
the two countries worked out a plan to put american accountants 
systems managers and computer experts recruited by the us 
agency for international development inside the liberian 
bureaucracy 
the operational experts nicknamed opex assumed their 
duties in january nine of the 17 went to the finance ministry 
its worked reasonably well one us official said summing 
up the eightmonthold experiment the benefits have been 
considerable already 
the official who insisted on anonymity said the twoyear 
program has exceeded the expectations of a lot of people who 
thought it would never get off the ground among other benefits 
civil servants are now being paid on time he said 
another official also speaking anonymously said before 
there was no government budget everything was entirely ad hoc 
opex has gotten the liberians to adhere to the budget its under 
pretty good control but there are still some financial flows 
outside the budget 
with the americans cosigning checks and taking over much of 
liberias economic management the plan gives the appearance of a 
liberian surrender of sovereignty in a key area which is a 
complaint voiced by liberian opposition leaders 
but the state department says doe still has the final say on all 
financial matters 
liberia may be the only country where it would be politically 
possible for the united states to play such an intrusive role but 
liberia with its red white and blue flag and its use of the us 
dollar as legal tender has always looked on the united states as a 
friend and patron 
the financial crisis can be traced back about 10 years when the 
liberian government decided to build a 200 million convention 
center it couldnt afford the country fell deeply into debt and 
the problems were compounded in 1980 when doe then a 28yearold 
sergeant took power in a military coup bringing with him a team 
of advisers with no government experience 
as prices of liberias principal exports fell foreign exchange 
earnings dropped eventually because of a poor debt repayment 
record the world bank and the international monetary fund declared 
liberia ineligible for new loans 
now as us officials describe it liberias future seems 
brighter and not only because of opex human rights violations are 
down liberias press is once again one of the freest in africa and 
there is increased demand for international demand for latex 
liberias major export 
concern about aids acquired immune deficiency syndrome has 
touched off a boom in sales of latex products such as condoms and 
gloves contributing to the more upbeat mood these days among 
liberians 
