applied only for state crimes because congress has not adopted the 
constitutional standards required to carry out capital punishment 
however coelho predicted that many democrats would back the 
death penalty and suggested the main party split would come over 
the gop plan to deny benefits to drug users 
to address complaints from local officials who said they never 
received promised antidrug grants the bill would require states 
to automatically pass through antidrug money to local governments 
banking law revisions would allow the government to closely 
watch institutions where drug money might be laundered 
recipients of federal grants or contracts would need to maintain 
a drugfree workplace 
money would be provided for drug education treatment and 
rehabilitation for aids victims and groups with a high risk of 
getting the disease 
