with uncharacteristic speed congress is 
expected in its final weeks to create a new law to combat what has 
become one of the biggest and most emotional problems of the summer 
of 88 medical waste that has invaded and shut down some of 
americas favorite beaches 
intense pressure from outraged citizens has driven congress to 
hold a series of public hearings including one this week on long 
islands jones beach and at least one measure and maybe more will 
be passed before the legislative year ends lawmakers and 
environmental activists predicted 
separate measures to create a waste tracking system and to 
