the increased flow on the mississippi also means a reduction in 
the number of bottlenecks that idled traffic upriver in june last 
week the coast guard relaxed restrictions on towboat loads that 
had been imposed earlier this summer because of low water levels on 
the lower mississippi 
the task of the clearinghouse on river conditions is to ensure 
that everyone on the river is informed of current developments 
smith said 
