more than onequarter of britains postal workers 
walked off their jobs monday as a nationwide mail strike spread and 
prevented the delivery of 65 million foreign and domestic letters 
and parcels 
three postal workers were arrested in liverpool one of 40 
cities where sorting offices were paralyzed by the strikes by 
48000 workers said the national post office royal mail 
royal mail which handles 51 million items of mail daily said 
the three were charged with disorderly behavior after bottles were 
thrown from a picket line at arriving temporary workers 
it was the first instance of violence in six days of strikes 
that began wednesday with a 24hour strike to protest regional pay 
differences 
the oneday strike officially ended but the issue of temporary 
workers hired to clear backlogs has continued to keep workers away 
from their jobs 
on monday london birmingham manchester liverpool edinburgh 
and glasgow were among cities where mail could not be collected 
posted sorted or delivered due to walkouts by 48000 of 140000 
sorting and collecting workers 
stamps could be purchased because 40000 administration and 
counter workers have not gone on strike 
international mail was completely suspended until further 
notice after walkouts at sorting offices for foreign mail in 
london and other cities said post office spokeswoman sally 
williams 
ms williams said although workers at londons heathrow airport 
office had gone back to work other offices were not in operation 
bill cockburn managing director of royal mail defended the 
hiring of 3500 temporary workers saying the number hired exceeded 
by only 500 the number used at other peak times such as christmas 
but alan tuffin general secretary of the union of 
communications workers said the dispute could escalate further 
and the whole system could be stopped by midweek 
ms williams said exploratory talks between the union and 
management were scheduled for monday night to see whether there 
is a basis for further negotiations union leaders met in 
england scotland and wales earlier monday to decide their course 
of action union officials said 
the strike wednesday centered on union objections to the post 
office offering weekly bonuses of 75 pounds to 20 pounds 1252 
to 3340 to recruit workers in london and southeast england 
the union said it would not tolerate regional pay differences 
and any bonuses should be paid nationally 
in another british labor dispute the trades union congress 
voted overwhelmingly monday to expel the electricians union its 
first ouster of an affiliate in 15 years 
