what should a corporate executive do 
spurred in part by complex new moral dilemmas and publicized 
incidents of criminal wrongdoing the harvard business school is 
requiring its 800 incoming students this fall to think about those 
and other ethical questions 
scholars said the threeweek minicourse at the 80yearold 
graduate school is part of a nationwide trend to devote more 
resources to teaching and research on moral reasoning and ethical 
values in corporate america 
its become sufficiently clear that the business leader of the 
future is going to have to be conversant and thoughtful about 
ethics said kenneth e goodpaster a philosopher who came to the 
harvard business school in 1980 to help develop an ethics 
curriculum 
one goal of the harvard course is to make future business 
leaders consider the impact of their decisions it joins philosophy 
with case study to stimulate dialogue on questions that defy easy 
answers 
the harvard course will tackle such topics as corporate 
responsibility in a plant relocation limits of economic reasoning 
in environmental waste issues conflicting cultural values in 
international business and organizational pressures against 
honesty and integrity 
what courses at harvard and other universities dont do is 
prescribe a set of morals you cant teach ethics scholars said 
graduate students bring with them values developed over a lifetime 
were not trying to make bad people all of a sudden turn into 
saints said joanne ciulla a philosopher who teaches ethics at 
the university of pennsylvanias wharton school its not coming 
up with the right answer its going through the process and 
understanding what are the issues and what are the values what do 
we have to think about here 
business ethics isnt a new field in 1915 harvard offered a 
class on social factors in business enterprise after the 1929 
stock market crash harvard hired a philosopher to teach ethics as 
society reacted to the depression by attacking greed in business 
wharton which has three ethics specialists this year for the 
first time is requiring students to attend two ethics sessions 
during orientation international business students take a class on 
crosscultural ethics while the graduate and undergraduate 
divisions have offered a business ethics course since 1975 
columbia universitys business school has required a course on 
social responsibility since the the mid1960s the university of 
virginia has had an applied ethics center for about 20 years and 
requires firstyear students to take a class similar to harvards 
while stanford offers an ethics elective 
with an increasing number of cases like the ivan boesky insider 
trading and the wedtech defense scandals those schools are 
intensifying research in ethics and harvard is hosting a 
conference on the subject in december still only about 10 percent 
of business students nationwide are required to study ethics 
harvard last year received a reported 20 million pledge from 
former securities and exchange commission chairman john shad to 
study ethics part of a universitywide program to boost research 
in the field in the professional schools 
scholars said the study of business over the last 30 years has 
become more scientific numberscrunching and bottomline analysis 
at the expense of ethics corporate purpose and corporate 
responsibility 
i dont have difficulty putting forth certain values where at 
least alarms ought to go off said thomas r piper harvards 
senior associate dean for education programs but i also think 
the emphasis should be on the awareness of the breadth of impact 
starting in the late 1950s and 60s business schools emphasized 
that the goal of a company should be maximizing the individual 
stockholders wealth now researchers talk about the impact of 
business decisions on all stakeholders workers communities 
customers future generations 
wherever you draw the line on insider trading meeting someone 
in an alley with 400000 in a suitcase is not a hard issue said 
r edward freeman director of the university of virginias olsson 
center of applied ethics 
the more important stuff is how do you put ethics in the 
center of business decisionmaking every day he said we try 
to make students understand that in every decision they make 
theyre making a moral choice 
